examples.en: You are answerable to him for it.
The agency is answerable to the governor.
Parents are answerable for their child's acts.
The results were not answerable to our hopes.
You are answerable for your own conduct at all times.
The success of their labours was answerable to the purity of their motives.
He was answerable with his head, if the King's army were not duly supplied.
He is answerable to Parliament for the conduct of the Armed Force.
They would be answerable with their lives for any further dereliction of duty.
